Four nucleic acid tests, a full Yin... MMD, even a woman can not help swearing!

Ps, those who say the sampling process is wrong, this is my own sample ~ ~ ~ 

Yes, I am referring to the eighth story in my colleague's father, the most real human being | the oral dictation of a Wuhan Smoking physician: The lives I've passed by. After more than a week of round-the-clock treatment and care, we still watched him slide into critical condition. Now his lungs were white and he could only live by the hour..

So far, I've been giving him high flow oxygen for two days, and it's not working so well. Oxygenation is barely in his 80s. 40-50 if you're not on high-flow oxygen, which is even more dangerous.

We deliver pure oxygen to the patient through a certain pressure, can reach pure oxygen breathing, this way is much higher than the comfort of suction machine, also not through mouth intubation, so the patient is very cooperative. After about three or five days, if his Oxygenation levels rise to normal, he'll survive respiratory failure.

Conversely, if the disease continues to progress, it will be non-invasive breathing machine, or even tracheal intubation connected with the creation of breathing machine. Non-invasive suction machine is based on the patient's breathing rate to breathe in, if the breathing rate is too fast, breathing machine will also respond to speed up the breathing rate, finally the patient prone to respiratory muscle fatigue, respiratory movement is not coordinated, resulting in human-machine resistance.

The patient now breathes more than 40 times (normal range for adult breathing is 12-20 times per minute) , and if he is intubated now, he is also at risk of becoming offline, worsening infection, and so on.

Extremely critical. So, the colleagues cry badly, I am also in collapse.

Some people say you doctors are so used to death and death, how can you still cry? Well, the question is, have you ever seen a patient with new pneumonia walk away

The Acute respiratory distress syndrome, lungs, heart, blood vessels, liver, kidneys and other organs were damaged... oxygen levels were not detected, heart rate, blood pressure dropped... quickly and quickly, but until the last few minutes, the patient was fully conscious.

As a result of sobriety, many patients will save, will cry out, doctor you save me... accompanied by a violent struggle, until the last breath.

For who in the scene, can endure this heart like a knife and tears like rain?

So, I've always said that this kind of goodbye to life is like drowning, as if your lungs were filled with water and you were dying, as if you were dying because of a gelatinous exudate from a new coronavirus. During this process, the lungs completely lose their ability to breathe, and no amount of oxygen can get into the blood, but other organs aren't failing as quickly, so it's painful and cruel. . .

Let us pray for miracles, even if there aren't many in the world.

1
Why not intubate a critical patient?

Many readers have asked why you don't intubate critical patients.

In simple terms, acute respiratory distress syndrome (ARDS) treatment is divided into four steps: the first step of high-flow oxygen treatment, if not on the non-invasive aspiration machine on the non-invasive aspiration machine, if the two hours of non-effective, tracheal intubation. At the end of the day, Ecmo if you can.

However, each step is preconditioned and standardized.

First of all, from the point of view of hardware, the prerequisite for tracheal intubation is to have a Laminar flow ward, after intubation, the ratio of medical care to reach 1:2 ~ 3.

Our current situation is that people with endotracheal intubation have a breathing machine and endotracheal intubation equipment, but there is no Laminar flow ward and it is impossible to deploy manpower according to regulations. There is a negative pressure Laminar flow ward in the General Icu of our hospital, but it only has a single isolation bed. It is no exaggeration to say that only one of our 1,000 beds in our top 3 hospitals is adequate for Endotracheal intubation for new coronary patients. And the patient who was in there hasn't been discharged.

Modification? In my opinion, it would take more than a week to convert a general ward into a Laminar flow ward, with such a Laminar flow sterilizing device and even the ceiling would have to be tilted open.

What if there's no hard drive? It's simple. Once the patient is intubated, all of our doctors and nurses will be shot. Take the simple bedside operation of "suctioning" for example, the nurse suctioning should be very common right? This procedure also has a high probability of infection, during sputum aspiration patients are stimulated, a cough aerosol directly out ~ ~ 

Endotracheal intubation clearly requires more room to maneuver. After the INTUBATION, it was like 24-hour continuous spraying of a new coronavirus aerosol. The air in the whole room would be polluted. Therefore, this high-risk, high-exposure operation, in the General Ward is not allowed, this is also the SARS before left us a bloody lesson.

Second, even with the right hardware and the right hands, endotracheal intubation is not the best option right now.

I'm just an average, run-of-the-mill doctor, and that's just a point of reference. It's like the top respiratory and critical care specialists in the country are in Wuhan.

However, the latest guidelines and consensus among experts shared through in-house channels, both non-invasive and invasive, do little to reverse the disease. A lot of patients, if they're intubated, they're basically Dead Tone, and only about 10% of them survive.

As a result, most people with endotracheal intubation (and invasive breathing) are less optimistic. Because tracheal intubation on the one hand will increase the patient's pain, increase the stimulation of the body, but also may lead to respiratory-related pneumonia. Once combined with inhalation-related bacterial infections, that's really scary, bacteria plus viruses, it's even harder.

Some friends might point to the case at Zhongnan Hospital that was saved by ECMO. But, as my colleagues and I have discussed, it is generally agreed that this may be an isolated case. Have you not heard of,. Therefore, at present, we still recommend high flow of oxygen on high flow of oxygen, can not intubate on not intubate, try to bring the patient in the earliest time. When it comes down to it, there's not much chance of a reversal.

2
How many lives CAN ECMO save?

We have to start with what an ECMO is.

ECMO is essentially an improved heart-lung machine. The core components are the membrane lung and the blood pump, which act as an artificial lung and heart respectively, and can provide long-term cardiopulmonary support to patients with severe heart-lung failure, to buy valuable time for critical care. In Layman's terms, when a patient's lung fails, I get an artificial lung to replace it, just like a dialysis machine.

As the core support means of severe heart and lung failure, this machine is usually used in cardiothoracic surgery to do major surgery, we generally won't easily into this equipment, one is more expensive, after all, SARS is not a very common disease.

As you can see, treating patients through ECMO only improves oxygenation. Now that the lungs are dead, even if we survive ECMO day by day, it's going to be a question of getting out of this machine..

Recently, morticians from many places went to Hubei to support them. "The half Moon Talk" published an article saying, "don't pull flags at any time! "

The lung is White, after easy fibrosis, what does fibrosis mean? It can't be reversed unless it's a lung transplant. Just like after Li Wenliang left, "In recent years, we have treated many other viral infections, such as Adenovirus, followed by co-infection with bacteria, and ECMO was turned around when the disease was critically ill. Finally, after treatment, the infection was controlled, nucleic acid turned negative, no bacteremia, but the fibrosis of both lungs became solid and could not be reversed by ECMO, " Chen Jingyu, a well-known lung transplant specialist, wrote in a post on a friend's circle. "We have evaluated lung transplantation in this group and we have had many successful long-term lung transplant survival cases. One patient survived the transplant for up to 45 days after the operation. "

In summary, the end result of inflammatory exudate is organization, and the result of organization may be fibrosis.

So, when it does come to white lung, even if the patient can still rely on Ecmo for 10 and a half days, or even 20 days, 45 days, chances are it's going to be a drain, a drain on resources.

To sum up, one is not allowed for software and hardware, the second is not very strongly recommended by the consensus of experts. So now we have to fight with millet rifles.

3
WHY DOES CT make a lot of double white lung?

What makes new coronary pneumonia so scary, besides being highly contagious, is the risk of developing a serious illness, Acute respiratory distress syndrome. SARS is acute severe respiratory syndrome, PS.

As mentioned earlier, the cause of death in severe cases of NCP is essentially the same as drowning. It's like drowning, when a lot of water gets into your lung tissue, and it takes up space in your lungs, so you can't get oxygen in.

If you don't understand it, take a look at the anatomy of the lung, as if it were a "bronchial tree" , with the trunk as the main Bronchus, the branches as the Bronchioles, and the small branches as the terminal bronchioles, the leaf is called a respiratory system.

How important are the Alveoli? It is the main part of the lung for Gas Exchange, for the multi-faceted open vesicles. The bubble wall is thin, the diameter is about 200 ~ 250 microns, the adult Alveolus has about 700 million, the total area may reach 100 meters!

The tissue between the adjacent Alveoli is called the Alveoli Septum and is rich in connective tissue such as capillary, elastic fibers, reticular fibers, and Collagen fibers. One side of the Alveoli is open to the Alveoli and the Bronchi; the other side is closely connected to the connective tissue and blood vessels of the Alveoli Septum, the Alveoli, the Alveoli Septum and the capillary, medically known as the air blood barrier, which is used by the body for the exchange of gases, that is, the exchange of oxygen in the Alveoli with carbon dioxide in the capillary. After the patient was infected with the new coronavirus, the airways at all levels were open, but the Terminal Airways were filled with inflammatory exudate, and with the Alveolar Septa widening, so the path of oxygen to our blood vessels was blocked, can't even get into our bloodstream, our patient goes into respiratory failure.

In short, the disease is mainly associated with Alveoli. The ALVEOLI are filled with viral inflammatory exudate, a gelatinous exudate, and sputum aspiration does not reach the terminal by bronchoscopy. So if it becomes serious, there's only so much a doctor can do.

From a microbial perspective, the new coronavirus, including SARS, is the most potent in the viral world for causing acute respiratory distress syndrome (ARDS) . Therefore, the current treatment is also basically according to the hoards syndrome to carry out. There is no specific drug, we doctors can do is to intervene in this process, intervene in the process of respiratory failure. Of course, we have to rule out other underlying diseases of the heart and lungs that cause ARDS.

[ image above taken from public call "Lotus seed job" ]

So why, one wonders, did the CT show white lung?

It's easy —— because the Alveoli are filled with this inflammatory exudate, and the Alveoli are all over the surface of the lung, underneath the lung capsule, from top to bottom, in every part, the surface of the lung that you can touch is filled with Alveoli. So according to the CT, one look is all white color.

This virus is really bad, don't be careless, don't relax, don't go to the supermarket, don't go downstairs to grab cabbages... the cow cow mother's last four pieces of advice, for everyone to feel as if

First, early diagnosis and treatment, do not drag into serious disease.

Second, can eat eat more, nutrition support is very important, enhance immunity.

Third, try to maintain a positive attitude, excessive anxiety will affect the efficacy.

4. Mild cases need regular re-examination to rule out residual fibrosis and avoid irreversibility.

"We have evaluated lung transplantation in this group and we have had many successful long-term lung transplant survival cases. One patient survived the transplant for up to 45 days after the operation. "

In summary, the end result of inflammatory exudate is organization, and the result of organization may be fibrosis.

So, when it does come to white lung, even if the patient can still rely on Ecmo for 10 and a half days, or even 20 days, 45 days, chances are it's going to be a drain, a drain on resources.

WHY DOES CT make a lot of double white lung?

What makes new coronary pneumonia so scary, besides being highly contagious, is the risk of developing a serious illness, Acute respiratory distress syndrome. SARS is acute severe respiratory syndrome, PS.

As mentioned earlier, the cause of death in severe cases of NCP is essentially the same as drowning. It's like drowning, when a lot of water gets into your lung tissue, and it takes up space in your lungs, so you can't get oxygen in.

If you don't understand it, take a look at the anatomy of the lung, as if it were a "bronchial tree" , with the trunk as the main Bronchus, the branches as the Bronchioles, and the small branches as the terminal bronchioles, the leaf is called a respiratory system.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
How important are the Alveoli? It is the main part of the lung for Gas Exchange, for the multi-faceted open vesicles. The bubble wall is thin, the diameter is about 200 ~ 250 microns, the adult Alveolus has about 700 million, the total area may reach 100 meters!

The tissue between the adjacent Alveoli is called the Alveoli Septum and is rich in connective tissue such as capillary, elastic fibers, reticular fibers, and Collagen fibers. One side of the Alveoli is open to the Alveoli and the Bronchi; the other side is closely connected to the connective tissue and blood vessels of the Alveoli Septum, the Alveoli, the Alveoli Septum and the capillary, medically known as the air blood barrier, which is used by the body for the exchange of gases, that is, the exchange of oxygen in the Alveoli with carbon dioxide in the capillary. After the patient was infected with the new coronavirus, the airways at all levels were open, but the Terminal Airways were filled with inflammatory exudate, and with the Alveolar Septa widening, so the path of oxygen to our blood vessels was blocked, can't even get into our bloodstream, our patient goes into respiratory failure.

In short, the disease is mainly associated with Alveoli. The ALVEOLI are filled with viral inflammatory exudate, a gelatinous exudate, and sputum aspiration does not reach the terminal by bronchoscopy. So if it becomes serious, there's only so much a doctor can do.

From a microbial perspective, the new coronavirus, including SARS, is the most potent in the viral world for causing acute respiratory distress syndrome (ARDS) . Therefore, the current treatment is also basically according to the hoards syndrome to carry out. There is no specific drug, we doctors can do is to intervene in this process, intervene in the process of respiratory failure. Of course, we have to rule out other underlying diseases of the heart and lungs that cause ARDS.

So why, one wonders, did the CT show white lung?

It's easy —— because the Alveoli are filled with this inflammatory exudate, and the Alveoli are all over the surface of the lung, underneath the lung capsule, from top to bottom, in every part, the surface of the lung that you can touch is filled with Alveoli. So according to the CT, one look is all white color.
